  "text": "If it isn't recorded, then it didn't happen. That's a golden rule. So how confident are we that when incidents happen on site, management has done the due diligence. The recorded records as and when required. When there is that mock recall, that unannounced audit outside or physically visiting the site, how do we know? How can we be proactive about it? Executives need evidence that is time-stemmed, traceable, and defendable, even in terms of litigation. A digital platform transformed paper doubt into digital proof.",
